Bottle Rocket is a 1996 American crime comedy film directed by Wes Anderson. It was co-written by Anderson and Owen Wilson. In addition to being Wes Anderson's directorial debut, Bottle Rocket was the debut feature for brothers Owen and Luke Wilson, who co-starred with James Caan and Robert Musgrave.The film was a commercial failure but launched Anderson's career by drawing attention from critics. Director Martin Scorsese later named Bottle Rocket one of his top-ten favorite movies of the 1990s.Bottle Rocket is also the name of a short film directed by Anderson and starring both Wilson brothers and Musgrave—shot in 1992 and released in 1994—on which the feature-length film was based.The film was shot entirely in Dallas, Fort Worth, and Hillsboro, Texas.
